This course provides students the basic knowledge and basic skills to help and assist in case of a major accident, disaster and military conflict. Also, the structure of the medical services of defence forces in peace and war time is the topic of subject as well as  the amount  of medical assistance  in different phases of accidents.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to provide students the basic knowledge and basic skills to help and assist in case of a major accident, disaster and military conflict.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who graduated the course: 1. Knows the structure of the medical services of defence forces in peace and war time and undrestands the volume of providing medical assistance  in different phases of assistance. 2. Knows disaster organization and understands the principles of medical care as part of it. 3. Is able to enumerate a variety of human and natural types of disasters and types of major accidents.  4. Understands the injuries that occur with different mechanisms of traumatic event.  5. Is able to implement the initial triage and knows the principles of conducting a secondary triage.  6. Is able to give life-saving first aid and knows the principles of approaching the trauma patient.  7.  Knows the basic threat groups of TBK and basic first aid principles in case of damage caused by TBK. 8. Understands the necessity of the implementation of personal protective equipment in case of TBK and knows the protection levels of various protection gear.
